## 9. Delivery Phases

### Phase 1 — MVP Core (Weeks 1-4)
- Auth (email + Google + Apple)
- Stamp card + point card
- QR code scan (add stamps/points + redeem rewards)
- Basic merchant dashboard (create program, view clients)
- Basic push notifications (manual campaign + welcome)
- Free plan only

### Phase 2 — Marketing & Monetization (Weeks 5-8)
- Segmented campaigns (target by profile)
- Analytics dashboard (KPIs, retention, cohorts)
- Stripe integration (Pro + Business plans)
- Referral system
- Auto notifications (inactivity, expiration, reward available)
- Multi-language (i18n)

### Phase 3 — Advanced (Weeks 9-12)
- NFC support
- Geolocation + proximity notifications
- A/B testing for campaigns
- Multi-location support
- Public API for integrations
- VIP/Gold/Silver tiers

---

## 10. Validation Method

- QR code: Merchant displays QR at checkout, client scans in-app (or client shows their QR, merchant scans via dashboard/cashier mode)
- NFC: Client taps phone on NFC tag at merchant location (Phase 3)
- Each scan is cryptographically validated via secret key to prevent fraud

---

## 11. Security Considerations

- Row Level Security (RLS) on all Supabase tables
- Merchant can only access their own data
- QR codes use HMAC-signed tokens with short expiration
- Stripe webhooks for subscription state management
- Rate limiting on Edge Functions
- GDPR compliance: data export, deletion, consent management
